You could build a TEST with code similar to the following I haven't really looked into Windows systems but it should work for Solaris/Linix and other *NIX systems.

```
import java.io.*;
import java.io.InputStream.*;

public class IsPrivUser
{

    public static String read(InputStream input) throws IOException {
        StringBuilder sb=new StringBuilder();
        BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(input));
        String read;
        while((read=br.readLine()) != null) {
            sb.append(read);
        }
        br.close();
        return sb.toString();
    }

    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        String userName = System.getProperty("user.name");
        String output = null;
        String error = null;
        try {
            Process p = Runtime.getRuntime().exec("groups " + userName);
            output = read(p.getInputStream());
            error = read(p.getErrorStream());
            if (output != null) {
                System.out.println("output: <"+output+">");
            }
            if (error != null) {
                System.out.println("error: <"+error+">");
            }
            if (error == null || error.length() == 0) {
                if ( output.indexOf("root") != -1 ) {
                    System.out.println("userName "+ userName + " is privileged");
                } else {
                    System.out.println("userName "+ userName + " is NOT privileged");
                }
            } else {
                System.out.println("YIKES when checking userName "+ userName + " we had an error");
            }
        } catch (IOException e) {
            System.out.println("System is non-Unix/Linix/Solaris");
        }
    }
}

```

Root or privileged user on Unix/Linux/Solaris

```
root# id
uid=0(root) gid=0(root)
root# java IsPrivUser
output: <root other bin sys adm uucp mail tty lp nuucp daemon>
error: <>
userName root is privileged
root#
```

non-privileged user on Unix/Linux/Solaris

```
non-priv# id
uid=1015(crome) gid=1(other)
non-priv# java IsPrivUser
output: <crome : other>
error: <>
userName crome is NOT privileged
non-priv#
```

